quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,43,"And of them are some who look at thee - canst thou guide the blind, although they cannot see"
  10,44,"Verily, God wrongs not man at all, but men do wrong themselves"
  10,45,"And on the day when we will gather them together it will be as though they had not tarried save an hour of the day, they shall know each other. Lost are those who called the meeting with God a lie, and were not guided"
  10,46,"Either we will show thee something of that with which we threatened them, or we will take thee to ourself, for unto us is their return; then is God a witness to what they do"
  10,47,"Every nation has its apostle; and when their apostle comes to them, it is decided between them with justice, and they are not wronged"
  10,48,"But they say, 'When is this threat (to come), if ye tell the truth"
  10,49,"Say, 'I have no power over myself for harm or for profit, save what God will. Every nation has its appointed time; when their appointed time comes to them they cannot delay it for an hour or bring it on"
  10,50,"Say, 'Let us see now when the torment comes to you, by night or day, what will the sinners fain bring on thereof"
  10,51,And when it has fallen - will ye believe in it now!- And yet ye wish to bring it on
  10,52,"Then shall it be said to those who have done wrong, Taste ye the torment of eternity! shall ye be recompensed except for that which ye have earned"
  10,53,"They will ask thee to inform them whether it be true. Say, 'Aye, by my Lord! verily, it is the truth, nor can ye weaken him"